				<td colspan="2"><span>Ok, first, I am not a big raid bard, least not yet.  Too much going on IRL to spend that much time online all the time.
<br />

<br />
Second, I have said it before, I don't know how you guys who say that pulling will get you the skill ups are pulling, but it ain't working for me.  I have been doing LDoN almost exclusively since about 40ish.  I pull nearly all of the advs I do, and unless I do something seriously wrong, I don't get hit hardly at all.  It isn't unheard of for me to loose Virtue mid adv, and not mention it, since I have not been hit more than once per mob in the last 15 mobs.  I would have to do something really wierd like off tank all the adds myself to get hit enough to get my skill up.  But then I would have to get adds, to do that.
<br />

<br />
Tenosh on Prexus.</span></td>
